<seg id="1045">"Povray; supports two methods of super-sampling. the standard is an adaptive, non-recursive method; adaptive because the super-sampling depends on the neighbouring pixels. the second method is adaptive-recursive; recursively because each pixel is repeatedly split up and adaptive because the recursion depth depends on the calculated color values."</seg>
<seg id="1046">"if you choose the first method, POV-Ray tracks a ray per pixel. if the difference between color values exceeds the specified threshold, then both pixels are calculated by tracking a specific additional number of pixels with super sampling. if you set the depth value to 4, a grid of 4x4 additional points will be calculated, at a depth of 5 then 5x5 (25) additional rays per pixel."</seg>
<seg id="1047">"the difference between two pixels is calculated as follows: r 1, g 1 and b 1 are the values for red, green and blue of the first pixel, r 2, g 2 and b 2 are the values for red, green and blue of the second pixel. the difference is then:"</seg>
